<title>USA: Fremont General Corp implements stock option.</title>
<headline>Fremont General Corp implements stock option.</headline>
<dateline>SANTA MONICA, Calif 1997-03-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>Fremont General Corp said it implemented a stock option exercise program which included the repurchase of Fremont General common stock by the Company's employee benefit trust.</p>
<p>The program's purpose was to encourage its executive officers to increase their outright ownership of Fremont General common stock through the exercise of vested common stock options.</p>
<p>Under the program, the executive officers exercised outstanding vested common stock options to purchase approximately 1,263,000 shares of Fremont General's common stock.</p>
